  "army_notes": [
    {
      "name": "Tallarn Companies",
      "text": "A Tallarn army may contain any number of companies."
    },
    {
      "name": "Tallarn Company Upgrades",
      "text": "Each Core Formation may select 0-3 upgrades. Each Core Formation may not select each upgrade type more than once."
    },
    {
      "name": "Tallarn Support Formations",
      "text": "Two Support Formations may be selected for each Core Formation in your army list."
    },
    {
      "name": "Allied Forces",
      "text": "No more than 1/3 of the army's points may be spent on Allies."
    },
    {
      "name": "Rationale",
      "text": "This is a list attempting to create a Desert Rats WW1/2 light raider force. Forgoing heavier vehicles, light armour and infiltrators must be used to achieve activation superiority and maintain initiative. Think Lawrence of Arabia, but in SPAAAAAACE....",
      "raw_text": "This is a list attempting to create a Desert Rats WW1/2 light raider force. Forgoing heavier vehicles, light armour and infiltrators must be used to achieve activation superiority and maintain initiative. Think Laurence of Arabia, but in SPAAAAAACE...."
    },
    {
      "name": "Design Rationale",
      "text": "The core themes of this list are intended to focus on Light Infantry, and the Tallarn style of raid-based warfare.\nFor this end, this list lacks all of the normal Imperial Guard main battle tanks, war engines, heavy artillery, Deathstrikes, VTOL skimmers, etc.\nInstead it concentrates on a few core types of infantry, with an emphasis on snipers, and also cavalry and aircraft with an emphasis on close air support.\nWhat vehicles are present, are all either transports, or scouting/raiding type vehicles. Instead of heavy Titans in the Allies section, the Tallarn army only has access to the Questoris Knight. Again, this helps form part of the \"lighter, faster\" theme of the list."
    },
    {
      "name": "EpicUK Leman Russ Conqueror Option",
      "text": "Some players may prefer to use the EpicUK stats for the Leman Russ Conqueror.\nEpicUK version: AV 25cm, A:5+, C:6+, F:5+, Reinforced Armour, +1 to Action Tests for Double orders, 250 points for 6."
    }
